d 'XTPQCS': module to estimate Panel Quantile Regression with Common Shocks
d
d    xtpqcs estimates the fixed-effects panel quantile regression
d (FEQR) model	  using the unregularised Koenker (2004)
d concentration algorithm and reports the robust covariance matrix
d of {bf:Chiang, Galvao    and Wei (2026, arXiv:2602.19201)}, which
d remains consistent in the presence (or absence) of pervasive
d common time shocks	Bt that induce arbitrary cross-sectional
d dependence.	Why does this matter?  In macro/finance panels the
d residuals of different units are contemporaneously correlated
d because    common factors (business cycles, monetary policy, oil
d prices) affect everybody at the same time.  Classical FEQR theory
d    ignores this correlation, leading to downward-biased standard
d errors and over-rejection of the null.  xtpqcs eliminates this   
d problem. 
d
d KW: panel data
d KW: quantile regression
d KW: fixed effects
d KW: common shocks
d
d Requires: Stata version 14
d
d Distribution-Date: 20260329
d
d Author:   Merwan Roudane, NA
d Support: email  merwanroudane920@@gmail.com
d
f xtpqcs.ado
f xtpqcs.sthlp
